The first class I wanted to talk about is the Paladin. A very brief summary of Paladin we&rsquo;ve seen in the past. First they were tanks, but not sought after for raids due to there squishiness compared to a Warrior, and filled less a void than its bretherin the Shadow Night (Dire Lord). They, however, had great group utility with Def buffs and Proc abilities, but there heals still weren&rsquo;t strong enough to justify a raid filler over well a Healer! As time advanced so did the Paladin, it quickly became a AoE Machine, could negate damage, and lastley became Main Healer class, losing it&rsquo;s tank-esk sex appeal (imo). The length of time your image will detain an enemy in combat will increase based on your Wisdom and Charisma. (Both of these are effected by your stats, I chose both bc it&rsquo;s a great way to support your tank. Taking damage off him while generating no aggro of your own is awesome. I&rsquo;d make this a staple of this build so your seen as useful to the group because a Paladin is the only class that has this mechanic.) <span style=\"background: #333333; margin: 0px; line-height: 19.6px; font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; line-height: 19.6px; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 140%; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 140%; font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; color: #f9ba1f; line-height: 22.4px; font-family: Cinzel; font-size: 16px;\">8. Knight&rsquo;s Persuasion</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 140%; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; line-height: 140%; font-size: 14px; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; box-sizing: inherit; orphans: 2; widows: 2; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; color: #cccccc; line-height: 19.6px; font-family: 'Libre Baskerville',serif; font-size: 14px;\">You leverage your charismatic presence to persuade a target Humanoid to lay down their arms for the sake of peace. If successful, immediately ends combat and makes target Humanoid friendly towards you for a limited time. The higher your Charisma, the more likely a successful persuasion will occur. (Uses Wrath. If successful, restores the Wrath used and generates 1 Reckoning Point)( The ultimate support ability, using the enemies of Terminus against one another, doesn&rsquo;t get much better!) </span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 140%; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; line-height: 140%; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; color: #cccccc; line-height: 19.6px; font-family: 'Libre Baskerville',serif; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"margin: 0px; color: #f9ba1f; line-height: 22.4px; font-family: Cinzel; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; line-height: 22.4px; font-size: 16px;\">9.<span style=\"font: 9px/12.6px 'Times New Roman'; margin: 0px; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"margin: 0px; color: #f9ba1f; line-height: 22.4px; font-family: Cinzel; font-size: 16px;\">Brilliant Aegis</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 140%; font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; line-height: 140%; font-size: 14px; word-spacing: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; box-sizing: inherit; orphans: 2; widows: 2; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; color: #cccccc; line-height: 19.6px; font-family: 'Libre Baskerville',serif; font-size: 14px;\">You release a concentrated burst of celestial light, blinding your enemies for X duration. This ability can also serve as a brief light source in Atmospheres of supernatural darkness. (Generates Wrath)(I snuck in a 9<sup>th</sup> for this build. Blinding enemies and getting them to glance can be just as helpful as a heal!
